<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Aladain:
[B]The problem with the tholuxe reservation system, imo, is that everything is hand tailored to the 8 guilds that are currently on it.

You have to kill ragefire guild only TWICE with absolutely no help from another guild using a free slot, which there are 2 per rotation.  Once you've done this your guild is on the rotation.  Once your on the rotation you dont have to kill rage guild only anymore, in fact once there was a situation where only 6 people from their own guild showed up, and they got help from about 12 others.

The other thing that is junk about our rotation is the only people that are allowed to make any changes to the rules are the guilds on the rotation and the person that over-sees it, whom is in one of the guilds on the rotation.  Thankfully, the rage rotation "moderator" is pretty fair, but in general, this has started to make other guilds upset about having to conform to a rotation that they have absolutely no say so in.

Its really sad actually, I hope they work something different.  I wouldnt mind my guild being FFA on rage, but then I will be looked at as being FFA on everything and I dont want to do that, so I kinda have to conform to the powerful 8 for the time being.

Aladain[/B][/QUOTE]

